content:
Product SKU is now removed as a default sortable product field on search and category pages in new D2C stores to better support customer sort preferences. Sorting search results by Product SKU is more common in B2B stores than in D2C stores. You can continue to manually configure Product SKU as a sortable field in B2B and D2C stores, enabling you to sort results in ascending or descending order to find the products that youâ€™re looking for.

Where: This change applies to D2C Commerce in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.
title: Updating Sortable Product Fields in Salesforce
